The paper deals with the computational complexity of the C-Planarity Testing problem for clustered graphs, which is a problem related to graph visualization. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graph-width parameters, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions the nesting between clusters, which is a concept related to graph theory, making cs.GT (Graph Theory) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for faster algorithms, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
